d even if no life ever developed the history of water on Mars and where it went will help us understand conditions and climate changes on Earth Mars Rocks Music for the Red Planet Mars inspires many of today s musicians If you can think of other Mars references in the music you listen to please mailto marsoutreach jpl nasa gov let us know In the seventies during the time of the missions past viking html Viking missions to Mars David Bowie wrote a song called Life on Mars Britney Spears features the Martian terrain in her music video Oops I Did It Again Vangelis who wrote the music for the film Chariots of Fire is now writing music inspired by the missions present odyssey html 2001 Mars Odyssey mission The UK band Blur has written a song about Mars that might be the first music broadcast from the Red Planet in 2003 from the European Space Agency s Beagle 2 lander part of the missions future express html Mars Express mission The Transfixions have also written a song called Ares4 which tells of the day when humans might one day go to Mars FUN ZONE extreme index html Extreme Planet follow index html Follow the Water Mars Rocks life index html Life on Mars mystique index html The Martian Mystique kids index html Just for Kids credits index html Credits mailto marsoutreach jpl nasa gov Feedback privacy index html NASA Privacy Statement overview index html Overview science index html Science technology index html Technology missions index html Missions newsroom index html Newsroom classroom index html Classroom events index html Events gallery index html Gallery http www jpl nasa gov JPL Home index html Mars Home sitemap index html Sitemap search index html Search Last Updated 22 Feb 2001
